Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteIoInstance(25.10)                                deleteIoInstance(25.10)

Name
       deleteIoInstance - Deletes the specified I/O instance

Syntax
        deleteIoInstance

       [-help]

       -instName {<name1 name2 ...>}

       Deletes  the  specified  I/O  instance. You can use this command at any
       point in the design flow.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each  deleteIoInstance parameter. For a detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command: man deleteIoInstance

       -instName {<name1 name2 ...>}
              Specifies the name(s) of I/O instance(s) to be deleted.

              Data_type: list, required

Example
              * The following command deletes the specified I/O instance:

                deleteIoInstance -instName newIo

Related Information
              * addIoInstance

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

